Nominated Senator Martha Wangari wants Auditor General Edward Ouko to conduct a special forensic audit on how two Kenyan public universities invested millions of shillings to set up campuses in Rwanda and Tanzania.Wangari, a member of the Senate Public Accounts Committee, wants to know the number and locations of the campuses, the rationale behind opening them outside Kenya, the total cost of investment, consent from the Education ministry to invest and operate outside Kenya and whether the investment is in line with the statutes establishing the two universities.She also wants to know why Kenyatta University registered the Rwanda campus in the name of a private company. Wangari also wants a full list of the company s directors.She wants KU and Jomo Kenyatta University of Agriculture and Technology the vice chancellors to explain their investments in those countries.